bug.short_desc: Scroll container behaves incorrectly when user release mouse button out of browser

long_desc.thetext:
Scroll container behaves incorrectly when user drags a scroll thumb and releases a mouse button out of browser or out of document. After this action scroll container stops working.
Steps to reproduce: 1) Go to http://demo.qooxdoo.org/current/demobrowser/ . There is a tree with scroll at the left. 2) Drag a scroll thumb and release mouse button out of document (for example on browser toolbar) 3) Try to use scroll, click scroll buttons, use mouse wheel. It does not work.
